White House Chief of Staff, General John Kelly, held a press briefing where he discussed a range of topics. He addressed the President's frustration with the slow progress of the government and the media's misreporting of his actions. General Kelly also spoke about the situation in Puerto Rico and the President's tweet regarding the country. He emphasized that the US will stand with the people of Puerto Rico until they have recovered sufficiently. General Kelly also touched on Iran's nuclear threat, the US-India relationship, and the fight against terrorism. He concluded the briefing by stating that his role as Chief of Staff is to provide the President with well-thought-out options to help him make decisions that protect and advance America.